[{"id":"VR184667","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a spherical conductor inside a larger spherical conducting shell. The inner sphere carries a negative charge, and the outer sphere carries a positive charge.\" height=\"205\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR184667.g13.png\" width=\"200\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A spherical capacitor is constructed with a spherical conductor surrounded by a thin spherical conducting shell. The inner sphere carries a charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"negative Q\"><math alttext=\"negative Q\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mrow><mo>âˆ’</mo><mi>Q</mi></mrow></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and the outer shell carries a charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive Q\"><math alttext=\"positive Q\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mo>+</mo><mi>Q</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, as shown in the figure above. Which of the following correctly shows the electric field lines for the capacitor?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR184667_rubric","choicesHtml":["<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a spherical conductor inside a larger spherical conducting shell. Field lines are emitted radially outward from the center of the spheres, and extend beyond the outer sphere.\" height=\"200\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR184667.g15.png\" width=\"200\"></div>\n","<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a spherical conductor inside a larger spherical conducting shell. Field lines point inward towards the center from the outer edge of the larger sphere, to the outer edge of the smaller sphere.\" height=\"199\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR184667.g17.png\" width=\"200\"></div>\n","<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a spherical conductor inside a larger spherical conducting shell. Field lines point outwards from the center from the outer edge of the smaller sphere, to the outer edge of the larger sphere.\" height=\"200\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR184667.g19.png\" width=\"200\"></div>\n","<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a spherical conductor inside a larger spherical conducting shell. Field lines point inward toward the center, and begin outside of the spheres and end at the center of the spheres.\" height=\"200\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR184667.g21.png\" width=\"200\"></div>\n","<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a spherical conductor inside a larger spherical conducting shell. No field lines are drawn, and a note indicates that E equals 0 everywhere.\" height=\"235\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR184667.g22.png\" width=\"200\" /></div>\n"],"answer":1}]